WEBVTT

00:02.870 --> 00:06.473
- [sobbing]

00:06.507 --> 00:08.642
- Hey, roomie.
You doing okay, son?

00:08.675 --> 00:10.711
- [sniffs]

00:10.744 --> 00:14.448
I just learned
that my life guru is a fraud.

00:14.481 --> 00:16.483
Has that ever happened before?

00:16.517 --> 00:18.352
- You mean
the pterodactyl lady?

00:18.385 --> 00:20.120
- Yeah.
[breaks wind]

00:20.153 --> 00:21.388
Ow!
And my farts hurt.

00:22.489 --> 00:24.091
- Well, that's no fun.

00:24.124 --> 00:26.527
We'll get you on a healthy diet
tomorrow morning,

00:26.560 --> 00:30.164
starting with my famous
eggnog waffles.

00:30.197 --> 00:32.466
- Ooh, nice!

00:32.499 --> 00:34.268
Hey, is John gonna think
it's weird

00:34.301 --> 00:35.669
that I'm living
in his old bedroom?

00:35.702 --> 00:37.237
- You mean
you haven't told him?

00:37.271 --> 00:38.505
- No.

00:38.539 --> 00:41.175
Uh...I haven't seen him
since last Monday.

00:41.208 --> 00:43.243
[dramatic jazz music]

00:43.277 --> 00:45.379
Best of luck
with your new partner.

00:45.412 --> 00:47.314
- Ready?
- Let's go, partner.

00:47.347 --> 00:49.449
- [revs engine]

00:49.483 --> 00:51.018
Hold me tighter!

00:51.051 --> 00:52.386
Motorcycle!
- Ah!

00:52.419 --> 00:55.255
♪ ♪

00:55.289 --> 00:56.623
Uh, Lance?

00:56.657 --> 00:58.091
Lance!

00:58.125 --> 00:59.393
- Shut up.
I'm driving my motorcycle.

00:59.426 --> 01:01.495
- Lance, pull over!

01:01.528 --> 01:03.363
- Oh, no.
You gotta make a BM?

01:03.397 --> 01:05.299
- What?
- It means take a dump.

01:05.332 --> 01:07.000
- Yeah, yeah, no, thank you.
I know what it means.

01:07.034 --> 01:08.268
- Get on!

01:08.302 --> 01:09.403
We're gonna be late
to our first case.

01:09.436 --> 01:11.638
- Oh, Lance, there is no case.
- What?

01:11.672 --> 01:13.674
- I haven't had a case
in weeks.

01:13.707 --> 01:16.176
See, I just need David
to see that I don't need him.

01:16.210 --> 01:18.345
- But I wanna solve mysteries
and hurt people!

01:18.378 --> 01:19.546
- Let me give you
some gas money.

01:19.580 --> 01:20.781
- What?
- $5--$5?

01:20.814 --> 01:22.216
- What?
I took a week off

01:22.249 --> 01:23.684
Ruby Tuesday's for this?

01:23.717 --> 01:25.319
- I didn't ask you to do
anything like--

01:25.352 --> 01:28.622
- You owe me $900.

01:28.655 --> 01:31.225
- Wow, you make that much
as, what, a busboy?

01:31.258 --> 01:33.160
- Fuck that!
Brunch host!

01:33.193 --> 01:34.728
Just try getting seated
near the salad bar

01:34.761 --> 01:36.096
without showing Lance
the money.

01:36.129 --> 01:38.465
- Okay, but I don't have $900.

01:38.499 --> 01:42.069
- Then I guess you're working
for me this week, or else.

01:42.102 --> 01:44.438
- Okay.
- Or else I beat you up.

01:44.471 --> 01:46.507
- Yeah, I got it.
- Punching your body

01:46.540 --> 01:48.542
with my fists!

01:48.575 --> 01:49.743
Punch, punch, punch,
punch, punch.

01:49.776 --> 01:51.478
- Oh, oh, oh, stop it.

01:51.512 --> 01:54.114
[dramatic jazz noir music]

01:55.649 --> 01:57.417
♪ ♪

01:57.451 --> 01:59.186
- I'm banned for life
at Doogley's Pet World,

01:59.219 --> 02:00.654
so I need you to get me
cat food,

02:00.687 --> 02:03.657
bat food, snake shampoo,
and 100 frozen mice.

02:03.690 --> 02:05.325
- Wait, how are we gonna carry
all that on a motorcycle?

02:05.359 --> 02:06.627
- Duh!

02:06.660 --> 02:08.128
You're gonna buy me
a little red wagon.

02:09.329 --> 02:10.631
- I-I hope
this little red wagon

02:10.664 --> 02:12.399
makes your son
a little less angry.

02:12.432 --> 02:14.401
- Oh, he is not my son.

02:14.434 --> 02:17.237
- Wait, is that... Lance?

02:17.271 --> 02:19.439
- [laughing maniacally]
- Get out of here, Lance!

02:19.473 --> 02:22.342
You know you're banned
from my wagon kiosk!

02:22.376 --> 02:23.977
- Motorcycle!

02:26.513 --> 02:28.549
♪ ♪

02:28.582 --> 02:29.716
- [quavers]

02:31.685 --> 02:33.420
- I need wood, nails,
and a hammer.

02:33.453 --> 02:35.155
- Uh, okay, why?

02:35.189 --> 02:37.758
- [emphatically] I'm building
a ramp for my snake!

02:37.791 --> 02:39.459
- Uh, okay.
- Hey!

02:39.493 --> 02:41.495
Don't let Mr. Sutton know
you're buying for me,

02:41.528 --> 02:43.130
or he'll ban you too.

02:43.163 --> 02:45.299
I'll stay out of sight.

02:46.066 --> 02:47.668
- Ugh.

02:47.701 --> 02:51.171
Wood, nails, hammer.

02:51.205 --> 02:53.207
Oh, I bet David would like
to know

02:53.240 --> 02:55.042
about this sale
on cargo shorts,

02:55.075 --> 02:56.743
But--ugh, no.
Fuck him.

02:56.777 --> 02:58.745
[cell phone rings]

02:58.779 --> 03:00.314
Hey, Heather.
What's up?

03:00.347 --> 03:02.282
Oh, really, are you sure?

03:02.316 --> 03:04.284
[cell phone buzzes]
Hang on. I got another call.

03:04.318 --> 03:06.687
Hmm, unknown number.
Hello?

03:06.720 --> 03:09.122
- What the fuck are you doing
answering an unknown number?

03:09.156 --> 03:10.557
- I--should I hang up?

03:10.591 --> 03:12.426
- No, no!
I need to tell you something.

03:13.360 --> 03:14.394
Hurry up!

03:14.428 --> 03:17.297
♪ ♪

03:17.331 --> 03:19.633
- So Heather said
my houseboat fire

03:19.666 --> 03:22.035
was caused by a wiring problem.
- Who cares?

03:22.069 --> 03:23.537
- Well, that means
Kaydee Festermeyer

03:23.570 --> 03:25.072
didn't burn my houseboat down.

03:25.105 --> 03:26.440
- Nobody cares!

03:26.473 --> 03:28.308
- But it does mean
my insurance will pay out.

03:28.342 --> 03:29.443
I can rebuild my boat!

03:29.476 --> 03:30.644
- Do you have the money yet?

03:30.677 --> 03:33.747
- Well, no.
- So you're still mine.

03:34.281 --> 03:37.084
[low music playing]

03:37.117 --> 03:39.653
- No, Lance, I'm not getting
you into a strip club.

03:39.686 --> 03:41.221
- Whoa, whoa!

03:41.255 --> 03:42.589
Gentleman's club.

03:42.623 --> 03:44.057
But that's not why we're here.

03:44.091 --> 03:46.460
♪ ♪

03:46.493 --> 03:47.494
- [growls]

03:47.528 --> 03:48.529
- [quavers]

03:48.562 --> 03:53.066
♪ ♪

03:53.100 --> 03:55.369
- Get as much shit as you can,
and the good shit, too.

03:55.402 --> 03:57.404
He won't sell to me.
He says I'm too young!

03:57.437 --> 03:59.139
- [growls]

03:59.173 --> 04:00.507
- Oh, God.
This is insane.

04:00.541 --> 04:03.210
- It's called self-medication.

04:03.243 --> 04:05.212
And, uh, you know,
get a few extra for yourself.

04:05.245 --> 04:08.215
- Ugh.

04:08.248 --> 04:09.516
- Are any
of these throwing stars

04:09.550 --> 04:11.318
hypoallergenic?

04:11.351 --> 04:13.353
I have a sensitivity to nickel.

04:13.387 --> 04:17.724
- [grunting]

04:17.758 --> 04:19.293
Pretty dope, huh?

04:19.326 --> 04:20.594
Ninja!

04:20.627 --> 04:22.496
- [sighs]

04:23.463 --> 04:25.032
Ugh.

04:25.065 --> 04:27.100
Lance, this is the fourth
strip club parking lot--

04:27.134 --> 04:29.069
- Gentleman's club parking lot!

04:29.102 --> 04:30.571
- Fourth we've been to today.

04:30.604 --> 04:32.005
This is getting kind of bleak.

04:32.039 --> 04:33.740
- Oh, stop your whining,

04:33.774 --> 04:35.642
and Friday, I'll take you
somewhere nice.

04:35.676 --> 04:37.711
Yah!

04:37.744 --> 04:39.646
[soft jazz music]

04:39.680 --> 04:42.149
- [slurping loudly]

04:42.182 --> 04:45.052
See? Nice.
- [laughs]

04:45.085 --> 04:47.387
"Nice" is not the word
that I would choose.

04:47.421 --> 04:48.755
Ugh.

04:48.789 --> 04:50.624
- It reminds me of my dad.
- Hmm.

04:50.657 --> 04:52.292
- He was a gentleman.
- Oh.

04:52.326 --> 04:53.994
- I think he used to work
the door.

04:54.027 --> 04:56.096
Or maybe he was the DJ.
My mommy won't say.

04:56.129 --> 04:57.731
- Is your dad deceased?

04:57.764 --> 05:00.033
- How would I know?
Do I look like his doctor?

05:00.067 --> 05:01.468
I mean, do you know
if your dad is deceased?

05:01.502 --> 05:02.736
- Um, my dad is alive.

05:02.769 --> 05:04.671
- Well, good for him!

05:10.611 --> 05:14.414
- Um, my mom is deceased,
if that makes you feel better.

05:14.448 --> 05:16.717
- A little.
Was she cool?

05:16.750 --> 05:18.418
- Mm, yes.

05:18.452 --> 05:19.987
- Did she DJ
at a gentleman's club?

05:24.424 --> 05:26.693
- My mom used to bring me here
when I was young.

05:26.727 --> 05:29.229
This is where I learned
to read comic books outdoors.

05:29.263 --> 05:31.665
- Uh, I've been here before,
too, I think,

05:31.698 --> 05:33.467
maybe with my dad.

05:33.500 --> 05:36.103
Yeah, yeah,
I remember those swings.

05:38.305 --> 05:39.606
Push me, now!
- What?

05:39.640 --> 05:41.775
Can't you pump?
- You still owe me a day,

05:41.808 --> 05:43.277
but I'm all out of shopping,

05:43.310 --> 05:45.179
so you're my dad now.

05:45.212 --> 05:46.446
- Uh, this doesn't seem
healthy.

05:46.480 --> 05:48.382
- Dad for a day.

05:48.415 --> 05:49.650
- Oh, my God.

05:49.683 --> 05:52.586
- Don't make me make you
change my diaper, Daddy.

05:52.619 --> 05:54.688
- Ugh.

05:54.721 --> 05:56.990
- Higher!
Higher!

05:57.024 --> 05:59.293
Whee!
Oh, I'm flying!

05:59.326 --> 06:01.128
Watch me, Day Daddy!

06:01.161 --> 06:02.429
- Lance, be careful!

06:02.462 --> 06:04.231
- [thuds]

06:04.264 --> 06:07.167
- And then she threw me
in the hair pit

06:07.201 --> 06:08.769
and told me to apologize,

06:08.802 --> 06:11.705
but I said, "No way, Kaydee.
I'm right."

06:11.738 --> 06:13.707
- A hair pit?
Aw, sick!

06:13.740 --> 06:15.742
Your job is cooler
than I thought, Day Daddy.

06:15.776 --> 06:17.678
- Oh, well, thank you.

06:17.711 --> 06:20.581
[serene music]

06:21.348 --> 06:23.650
-
Uh, something's wrong.
I feel weird.

06:23.684 --> 06:25.252
- L--Lance, are you okay?
What do you mean?

06:25.285 --> 06:27.321
- Like, usually, my brain
is really noisy

06:27.354 --> 06:28.622
and I wanna punch something,

06:28.655 --> 06:30.390
like, I don't know,
your dumb face,

06:30.424 --> 06:33.494
but right now,
I feel quiet inside.

06:33.527 --> 06:35.729
- [laughs] Yeah.
That's called contentment.

06:35.762 --> 06:37.364
- Fuck!
I hate contentment!

06:37.397 --> 06:38.599
- Oh, Lance, why?

06:38.632 --> 06:40.100
- Because I'm supposed
to be angry!

06:40.133 --> 06:41.435
That's who I am!

06:41.468 --> 06:43.570
What if I wake up someday,
"content,"

06:43.604 --> 06:45.372
and I'm not Lance anymore,

06:45.405 --> 06:48.242
like that famous loser
who turned into a cockroach?

06:48.275 --> 06:51.044
- "The Metamorphosis"?
Lance, that wasn't real.

06:51.078 --> 06:52.412
- Then why'd they teach it
in school?

06:52.446 --> 06:54.314
- Lance, it was a metaphor,

06:54.348 --> 06:56.450
something that symbolizes
something else.

06:56.483 --> 07:00.087
- A metaphor.
Whoa, they can do that?

07:00.120 --> 07:03.257
- Lance, even if you stop
being angry,

07:03.290 --> 07:05.225
you'll still be Lance.

07:05.259 --> 07:08.128
You just won't be angry.

07:08.162 --> 07:10.030
- You know what?
You're right.

07:10.063 --> 07:11.565
- Well, I always am.

07:11.598 --> 07:12.766
- You're also full of shit.

07:12.799 --> 07:14.034
- What?
Excuse me?

07:14.067 --> 07:15.302
- You were wrong
about that woman

07:15.335 --> 07:16.603
burning your houseboat down.

07:16.637 --> 07:17.738
Why can't you be wrong

07:17.771 --> 07:19.339
about her stealing
that trophy, too?

07:19.373 --> 07:22.242
- No, I'm not wrong, Lance.
I have a mind palace.

07:22.276 --> 07:23.377
Perfect recall.

07:23.410 --> 07:25.345
That's why
I always get it right.

07:25.379 --> 07:26.580
That's who I am.

07:26.613 --> 07:27.714
- Bullshit!

07:27.748 --> 07:29.082
Why can't you take
your own advice?

07:29.116 --> 07:30.350
Right?
Uh, what'd you say?

07:30.384 --> 07:32.553
Even if you're wrong sometimes,
it's okay.

07:32.586 --> 07:34.054
You'll still be John Hunchman.

07:34.087 --> 07:36.757
- But I hate that guy!
[echoing]

07:39.226 --> 07:42.529
Being right is the only part
of me that I like.

07:44.464 --> 07:47.067
- You know what this is?
- Of course.

07:47.100 --> 07:49.169
Cambarus bartonii,
the common crayfish,

07:49.203 --> 07:50.537
or crawfish,
if you're in Louisiana.

07:50.571 --> 07:54.141
- Wrong again!
It's a metaphor for you.

07:54.174 --> 07:56.343
You have this hard shell
around you,

07:56.376 --> 07:59.146
but underneath,
you're soft and scared,

07:59.179 --> 08:00.514
like this guy,

08:00.547 --> 08:02.449
like me.

08:02.482 --> 08:06.086
- But periodically,
a crayfish has to molt,

08:06.119 --> 08:08.455
shed its shell
in order to grow.

08:08.488 --> 08:11.124
Lance, I think I'm ready
to shed my shell--oh!

08:11.158 --> 08:13.393
[raccoon snarling]

08:13.427 --> 08:14.595
- Is that thing rabid?

08:14.628 --> 08:17.364
[dramatic music]

08:17.397 --> 08:20.100
[raccoon hissing]

08:20.133 --> 08:22.703
[spacey music]

08:23.537 --> 08:26.240
Hello? Hello?

08:26.273 --> 08:29.009
Are you having a coma?

08:29.042 --> 08:31.111
- What is that?

08:31.144 --> 08:32.279
Hmm.

08:32.312 --> 08:34.248
[ominous rumbling]

08:34.281 --> 08:38.585
♪ ♪

08:38.619 --> 08:42.689
[rumbling]

08:42.723 --> 08:45.392
[straining]
Why can't I let go?

08:51.465 --> 08:53.033
Ah!

08:53.433 --> 08:54.735
- Ya
h!
[star thuds]

08:54.768 --> 08:57.337
I chased the raccoon off
with my throwing stars.

08:57.371 --> 08:58.639
- I was wrong.

08:58.672 --> 09:00.140
- Not before it ate
the metaphor, though.

09:00.174 --> 09:01.108
Wait, what'd you say?

09:01.141 --> 09:02.276
- I--I was wrong.

09:02.309 --> 09:03.610
The raccoon proves it.

09:03.644 --> 09:04.678
- Oh, I'm sorry.
Did a butterfly

09:04.711 --> 09:06.213
just whisper something
somewhere?

09:06.246 --> 09:07.481
Say it louder.

09:07.514 --> 09:09.149
- Kaydee Festermeyer
is innocent.

09:09.183 --> 09:10.551
I was wrong!
- Yes, yes!

09:10.584 --> 09:12.653
Now we're getting somewhere.
[phone beeps]

09:12.686 --> 09:14.221
Oh, okay.
It's 6:00.

09:14.254 --> 09:15.455
You're off the clock.
You need a ride somewhere?

09:15.489 --> 09:17.257
- No, I--I think I'm going
to walk around

09:17.291 --> 09:18.759
for a while and think.

09:18.792 --> 09:20.427
- Yeah, take this wagon.
I don't want it anymore.

09:20.460 --> 09:22.696
I think it might be a metaphor,
and it's freaking me out.

09:22.729 --> 09:24.498
- Okay.

09:26.667 --> 09:28.235
I want my dad.

09:29.636 --> 09:31.138
- [growls]
If I had known

09:31.171 --> 09:32.506
it was gonna take
so long to grow up,

09:32.539 --> 09:34.007
I would've started
a lot sooner.

09:34.041 --> 09:37.110
- [laughs] That's not
how it works, David.

09:37.144 --> 09:39.313
Growing up is like golf.

09:39.346 --> 09:41.481
- Do you mean if I get good
at golf, I'll be a grown-up?

09:41.515 --> 09:43.417
- [laughs] No.

09:43.450 --> 09:46.787
Growing up is like golf
because there are no shortcuts.

09:46.820 --> 09:49.189
You have to play every hole,

09:49.223 --> 09:51.091
and if you miss a hole,
move on.

09:51.124 --> 09:52.526
You hit one
into the water feature,

09:52.559 --> 09:53.627
you let it go.

09:53.660 --> 09:56.063
- Oh!
It's a metaphor.

09:56.096 --> 09:58.298
- Actually, I think it might be
a simile.

09:58.332 --> 10:00.167
- Fuck!

10:00.200 --> 10:02.102
I'm the stupidest person
in the world!

10:02.135 --> 10:03.370
- No, no, it's okay.
Forget about that.

10:03.403 --> 10:06.073
Just leave
pterodactyl lady behind

10:06.106 --> 10:07.241
in the water feature.

10:07.274 --> 10:10.744
Tomorrow is a whole new,
well, hole.

10:10.777 --> 10:13.480
- Huh.
Yeah, I like that.

10:13.514 --> 10:19.453
Mr. H, how would you feel
about a whole new hug?

10:19.486 --> 10:22.122
Mm!

10:22.155 --> 10:24.591
- [clears throat]
May I ask

10:24.625 --> 10:26.160
what in the living fuck
is happening?

10:26.193 --> 10:27.327
- Hey, bud!

10:27.361 --> 10:29.196
I was just comforting
my roomie.

10:29.229 --> 10:31.165
- My dad
is your cool new roommate?

10:31.198 --> 10:33.033
- Oh, my God, dude,
he's the best.

10:33.066 --> 10:34.434
- You wanna get in
on this hug?

10:34.468 --> 10:35.736
- Bring it in!
[breaks wind]

10:35.769 --> 10:37.371
Ow!

10:37.404 --> 10:39.239
- No, thank you.
I'm taking my little red wagon

10:39.273 --> 10:42.309
and going downstairs.

10:42.342 --> 10:45.646
[wagon thudding on stairs]

10:57.224 --> 11:00.227
Made in Georgia
